    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Michel Rivard"
      },
      {
        "@language": "fr",
        "@value": "Michel Rivard"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/inLanguage": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": ""
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "APRÈS, ON VA OÙ ? – Michel RivardA Solitary Musical Theatre Experience\r\nOver the course of two symbolic weeks - the brief, breathtaking bloom of a magnolia outside his bedroom window - “the man who looks like me” (74 years old) reflects on the journey of a life fully lived.\r\nBetween doctor’s appointments and choosing an urn from a catalogue, between memories of first love and a walk in the forest with his seven-year-old grandson, he moves through time with honesty, humour, and tenderness. In this intimate solo performance, he questions everything: life, death, doubt, certainty and what might lie beyond.Through spoken word, poetry, and song, Michel Rivard guides us on a deeply human search for something larger than oneself - fragile, profound, and unexpectedly uplifting.\r\nText, songs, and performance: Michel RivardMusicians: François Richard, Blanche Baillargeon, and Guillaume Bourque\r\nPerformance in French. "
      },
      {
        "@language": "fr",
        "@value": "APRÈS, ON VA OÙ ? - Michel Rivardthéâtre musical en solitaire\r\nDurant les deux semaines (symboliques) que dure la magnifique floraison du magnolia qui illumine la fenêtre de sa chambre, « l'homme qui me ressemble » (74 ans) se questionne sur sa vie, avant et après la mort, en confrontant ses doutes et ses certitudes.\r\nEntre un rendez-vous médical et le choix d'une urne dans un catalogue, entre un premier amour et une marche en forêt avec son petit-fils de sept ans, « l'homme qui me ressemble » monologue, poétise et chante sa recherche du « plus-grand-que-soi ».\r\nTexte, chansons et interprétation : Michel RivardMusiciens.nes : François Richard , Blanche Baillargeon et Guillaume Bourque. "
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/eventAttendanceMode": [
      {
        "@id": "http://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/eventStatus": [
      {
        "@id": "http://schema.org/EventScheduled"
      }
    ]
  },
